<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-12T01:36:00-05:00" n="1296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1296">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/43.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guadalajara</hi>
                                </placeName> (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1914-01-12T00:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received January 14,
                                    1914</hi>).</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Legislature State of Michoacan has decreed a forced loan equalling
                            one year taxes to support federal troops in that state claiming the
                            money will be returned. Several Americans here owning property in that
                            state want to know if they have to comply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>